title: Oregon State DB Decoud taken from game in ambulance
text:
Oregon State defensive back Treston Decoud taken from game against Colorado by ambulance THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   25, 2015 - 12:07 amLast Updated: October 25, 2015 - 12:09 am   
Organizations: 
Oregon (411) 

CORVALLIS, Oregon — Oregon State defensive back Treston Decoud was taken from the field in an ambulance Saturday night during the Beavers' game against Colorado. 
Decoud was injured early in the second quarter after an inadvertent hit by a teammate. He was immobile on the turf for several minutes before he was placed on a stretcher and loaded into the ambulance on the field. 
The extent of his injury was not immediately known. 
Decoud, a junior transfer from Northwest Mississippi Community College, started in six of the Beavers' games this season. He has 28 tackles and four pass breakups.
